71
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:55,000
COVID-19 outbreak in this Huanan seafood market. But the issue is, there were hundreds of samples that were taken to the Wuhan Institute of Virology. The database that housed these samples was taken offline weirdly a couple of months before the known start of the COVID-19 outbreak. So we're, you know, publicly, we're taking samples from the

72
00:18:55,000 --> 00:19:23,000
whole universe of samples that emerged from that mine. Now, based on the fact that the Wuhan Institute of Virology collaborated with a number of US institutions, most notably, presumably the University of North Carolina, which I think we'll get to. Can we look at any of the grants or publications that came out of those jointly and surmise just how many samples were taken?

73
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:31,000
Can we surmise just how many samples of coronaviruses were extracted from 2013 until 2019?

74
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:52,000
Yeah, I mean, well, we know that there are hundreds, hundreds of samples that were extracted. And we presume that there was, you know, deep sequencing done on these samples. But again, we don't have access to all that information.

75
00:19:52,000 --> 00:20:05,000
So, you know, we don't know if, if any of those other samples may have closed the gap from 96.2 to 100%, basically.

76
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:29,000
So again, just to ground everybody in the thought process here, if, if there's an argument to be made that that SARS-CoV-2 originated, in its final origination came from a lab, you basically have a couple of mechanisms that that could have happened.

77
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:47,000
One would be that the exact version of SARS-CoV-2 was identified in the wild, potentially in this mine, was brought to the lab where it was being studied, but not altered before it infected, presumably a lab worker that ultimately led to the outbreak.

78
00:20:47,000 --> 00:21:04,000
Conversely, a very, very, very close cousin to SARS-CoV-2 was identified in the wild, again, potentially in this mine, where it was brought to the lab. And research was done on it, which we'll get to called gain-of-function research.

79
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:19,000
And that closed the genetic gap, so to speak, from where it started to where it currently is, and what ultimately led to the outbreak through presumably some contamination within the lab.

80
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:24,000
Is that sort of a safe summation of the plausible scenarios?

81
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:46,000
That is. And, you know, let me just add that the reason those scenarios exist as questions that remain unanswered is because there has been a fundamental lack of transparency that has essentially been enforced by the Chinese government.

82
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:55,000
And I mean there to distinguish between the motives of the scientists and the motives of the government.

83
00:21:55,000 --> 00:22:09,000
We don't know whether the Chinese scientists would like a full accounting of everything that happened and are being prevented at giving one because the government is restricting it.

84
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:18,000
So, you know, we really, the questions can't be resolved because there hasn't been transparency around them.

85
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:31,000
