96
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:58,000
How does it infect? Is it going to become more infectious? And by what mechanism is it going to become more infectious?

97
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:19,000
So gain-of-function research, put simply, is this idea that you are trying to test whether the pathogen can become more infectious. You're trying to give it attributes that it doesn't possess in nature as a way to gauge its own

98
