effect, to gauge its infectiousness to humans. Yeah, sorry. Go ahead.

99
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:49,000
No, no. I was just going to say, look, at the surface, I think if you're listening to this and you don't dabble in this world, that sounds a bit absurd, right? We're going to take a virus that may have a certain level of either virulence or lethality or transmissibility, some feature that makes a virus undesirable, and we're going to enhance that.

100
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:58,000
So what's the argument for doing that? What's the argument for making a bad virus worse or making a good virus bad?

101
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:19,000
So, you know, first of all, let me say this is hugely controversial and has sort of divided the field of virology because there are people who say this is absolutely crazy. You know, as one source said to me, it's like it's like looking for a gas leak with a lighted match.

102
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:41,000
