149
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:47,000
Yeah, so, you know, it's important to note it was not a peer reviewed paper. It was a statement, which was published by 27 scientists who said basically anybody who is saying that this could have had a lab origin is siding with is trafficking in conspiracy theories.

150
00:40:48,000 --> 00:41:11,000
And we stand with our fellow scientists in China to say that this had a natural origin. It was a big piece of branding, right, that suddenly raising the question of the lab leak was aiding and abetting Donald Trump's xenophobic agenda, aiding and abetting conspiracy theorists.

151
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:21,000
And as one of my sources said, it was like it was nailed to the church door. It became the orthodoxy and it really shut down debate.

152
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:30,000
But there was something more consequential that emerged from that Lancet statement. The scientists who signed it asserted that they had no conflicts of interest.

153
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:41,000
The problem was the person who had sort of designed and orchestrated the statement was Peter Daschak, who is the president of EcoHealth Alliance.

154
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:48,000
